============================================================

Written the improvement plan. Here's the summary:

**Failure 1 (LABANEH):** Add a **short ALL_CAPS line merge pass** early in `buildCandidates`. When consecutive ALL_CAPS lines each have ≤2 words and ≤25 chars, coalesce them into a single logical line before any candidate generation. This assembles `LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA SEEDS` as a single candidate at position 0, bypassing both the 3-line join ceiling and the dedup problem entirely. Safe because mixed-case lines, section labels, and multi-word heading lines (like CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM) are never merged.

**Failure 2 (Smażona zielona fasolka):** Add a **layout-based bilingual detection fallback**. When embedding similarity fails to detect a cross-lingual pair (Polish ↔ Korean romanization), fall back to a positional heuristic: mixed-case ≥2-word candidate at position 0 + ALL_CAPS ≥2-word candidate at position 1-2 with no words in common → suppress the ALL_CAPS candidate. This eliminates dependence on cross-lingual embedding quality while staying safe for single-language pages (where titles would share vocabulary).

Both changes are ~30 and ~15 lines respectively, touch only `title-extractor.ts`, and don't modify the dedup logic, scoring formula, or multi-title guard.
