{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013AueKzNjXyX8RXMsYNzzbJ","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive data across iterations 10–14. Let me compile the summary.\n\n## Summary: Approaches Tried and Recurring Failure Patterns\n\nBased on the feedback and improvement plans from iterations 10–14, here are the approaches taken and recurring failure patterns in the title extraction loop:\n\n### **Approaches Tried**\n\n**Iteration 10** (Polish metadata patterns):\n- Added Polish serving-size patterns (`NA N`, `DLA N`) and time-unit metadata (`N MIN`, `N GODZ`) to `looksLikeMetadata`\n- Added structural heading selection tiebreaker (prefer longer candidates when embedding scores are close)\n- Added pre-dedup sub-section header filter (remove ALL_CAPS headers followed by ingredients when a longer candidate contains them)\n\n**Iteration 11** (Bilingual detection robustness):\n- Added pipe-separator filter (`text.includes(\" | \")`) to exclude book category headers from candidates\n- Added structural heading guard to bilingual suppression (preserve `firstStructuralHeading` even when suppression fires)\n- Broadened pre-dedup section filter to check `rawScored` instead of just `selected` for longer parent candidates\n\n**Iteration 12** (Ingredient and section label filtering):\n- Added bullet-line filter (`/^\\s*[-•*]\\s/`) to exclude ingredient lists from candidates at the hard-filter stage\n- Added section label filter (`SECTION_LABELS` constant) to exclude words like `INGREDIENTS`, `SKŁADNIKI`, `DIRECTIONS`, etc.\n- Expanded `looksLikeIngredient` to cover Polish measurement units (`łyżka`, `szklanka`, `szczypta`), compact metric notation (`100g`, `50ml`), and qualitative patterns (`to taste`, `do smaku`)\n\n**Iteration 13–14** (Consolidation, but new issues):\n- All previous fixes preserved\n- Iteration 14 revealed two new failure modes despite fixes passing iteration 13 tests\n\n---\n\n### **Recurring Failure Patterns**\n\n#### **Pattern 1: Multi-word titles broken across OCR lines**\n- **Appears in:** Iteration 14 (Labaneh Balls with Nigella Seeds)\n- **Issue:** When OCR splits a title across 4+ lines, the algorithm only generates joins up to 3 consecutive lines. The full title never enters the candidate pool. Shorter overlapping fragments then win via dedup (\"shorter wins\" rule).\n- **Why it recurs:** The 3-line join ceiling has been constant since iteration 1. This is a design constraint, not a bug in recent changes.\n\n#### **Pattern 2: Structural bonus overrides mixed-case legitimate titles**\n- **Appears in:** Iteration 14 (Smażona zielona fasolka), indirectly in earlier iterations\n- **Issue:** The +0.10 structural heading bonus for ALL_CAPS candidates is enough to flip the winner when the true title is mixed-case (Polish, Italian convention). An all-caps secondary title line (translation/subtitle) beats the actual mixed-case title.\n- **Why it recurs:** The structural bonus is a global constant. It was tuned to prefer all-caps recipe headings (which are common in English cookbooks), but it creates systematic bias against non-English typography conventions.\n\n#### **Pattern 3: Bilingual detection threshold is fragile and narrow in scope**\n- **Appears in:** Iteration 11 (CHLEBEK false positive), Iteration 14 (Smażona zielona cross-lingual pair)\n- **Issue:** The 0.4 cosine similarity threshold for detecting translation pairs only works reliably for closely related language pairs (Polish ↔ English). Cross-lingual pairs like Polish ↔ Korean romanization fall below 0.4. The detection also only checks position 0 (mixed-case) + positions 1–2 (all-caps), so it misses translations at other positions.\n- **Why it recurs:** The threshold is a magic constant calibrated against a narrow set of examples. New language combinations expose its brittleness.\n\n#### **Pattern 4: Incomplete ingredient/list detection**\n- **Appeared in:** Iteration 12 (12 bullet-line failures)\n- **Status:** Fixed by changes in iteration 12 (bullet filter + section label filter + expanded `looksLikeIngredient`)\n- **Note:** The fix was comprehensive at the candidate-generation stage, so it does not recur in iterations 13–14.\n\n#### **Pattern 5: Dedup \"shorter wins\" removes valid longer candidates**\n- **Appears in:** Iteration 14 (WITH NIGELLA substring of LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA)\n- **Issue:** The dedup rule unconditionally prefers shorter candidates when one is a substring of another. This is correct for `Pierogi Ruskie` vs. `Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki`, but breaks when a shorter overlapping substring is a semantic fragment (never intended to be a title) rather than a more focused version of the same title.\n- **Why it recurs:** The dedup rule is a core heuristic that has been stable since iteration 5. Recent fixes (iteration 11–12) added guards to prevent sub-section headers from entering the pool in the first place, but they don't address the dedup rule's blind spot: overlapping candidates where neither is a clean parent/child relationship.\n\n#### **Pattern 6: Multi-title guard assumptions**\n- **Appears in:** Iteration 12 (section label `INGREDIENTS` wins), earlier iterations\n- **Issue:** The `isSubHeader` check assumes the first ALL_CAPS heading is the recipe title and checks only the remainder as potential sub-headers. This breaks when document layout is `SECTION_LABEL → TITLE → ingredients`.\n- **Status:** Fixed by section label filter in iteration 12, removing section labels before they reach the multi-title guard.\n\n---\n\n### **High-Level Patterns**\n\n1. **Language-specific gaps:** Each iteration uncovers patterns absent from previous language coverage (Polish measurement units, Polish metadata, non-English capitalization conventions).\n\n2. **Threshold brittleness:** Magic constants (`0.4` similarity, `+0.10` structural bonus, `3-line` join ceiling) work for the corpus they were tuned against but break on edge cases.\n\n3. **Cascading precondition dependencies:** Downstream guards (dedup, multi-title guard, prefix removal) often depend on upstream conditions (full title presence in `selected`). When an earlier stage suppresses the full title, later guards become ineffective.\n\n4. **Structural heuristics vs. content signals:** The algorithm increasingly relies on typographic structure (ALL_CAPS, section positions, bullet markers) to avoid embedding-score errors, but structure is language/cookbook-specific. Non-English cookbooks and OCR-mangled formatting break these assumptions.\n\n5. **OCR fragmentation:** The 3-line join ceiling and pre-merge continuation logic handle some line breaks but not arbitrary multi-line splits of titles."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1f1357a92987983e (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 76596\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 32010</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ac343373-92a8-4ed5-8825-039c81cffb50","uuid":"11f1a52c-87b1-481f-b4da-cd47de410e81","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the improvement plans and feedback from recent iterations of the title extraction loop. Read these files:\n- tools/title-loop/docs/13-84a8421/feedback.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/12-0b9bd80/feedback.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/11-023af39/feedback.md\n- tools/title-loop/docs/10-d73df28/feedback.md\n\nAlso read any improvement-plan.md files in those directories if they exist.\n\nSummarize: what approaches have been tried and what patterns of failures keep recurring?","agentId":"a1f1357a92987983e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have comprehensive data across iterations 10–14. Let me compile the summary.\n\n## Summary: Approaches Tried and Recurring Failure Patterns\n\nBased on the feedback and improvement plans from iterations 10–14, here are the approaches taken and recurring failure patterns in the title extraction loop:\n\n### **Approaches Tried**\n\n**Iteration 10** (Polish metadata patterns):\n- Added Polish serving-size patterns (`NA N`, `DLA N`) and time-unit metadata (`N MIN`, `N GODZ`) to `looksLikeMetadata`\n- Added structural heading selection tiebreaker (prefer longer candidates when embedding scores are close)\n- Added pre-dedup sub-section header filter (remove ALL_CAPS headers followed by ingredients when a longer candidate contains them)\n\n**Iteration 11** (Bilingual detection robustness):\n- Added pipe-separator filter (`text.includes(\" | \")`) to exclude book category headers from candidates\n- Added structural heading guard to bilingual suppression (preserve `firstStructuralHeading` even when suppression fires)\n- Broadened pre-dedup section filter to check `rawScored` instead of just `selected` for longer parent candidates\n\n**Iteration 12** (Ingredient and section label filtering):\n- Added bullet-line filter (`/^\\s*[-•*]\\s/`) to exclude ingredient lists from candidates at the hard-filter stage\n- Added section label filter (`SECTION_LABELS` constant) to exclude words like `INGREDIENTS`, `SKŁADNIKI`, `DIRECTIONS`, etc.\n- Expanded `looksLikeIngredient` to cover Polish measurement units (`łyżka`, `szklanka`, `szczypta`), compact metric notation (`100g`, `50ml`), and qualitative patterns (`to taste`, `do smaku`)\n\n**Iteration 13–14** (Consolidation, but new issues):\n- All previous fixes preserved\n- Iteration 14 revealed two new failure modes despite fixes passing iteration 13 tests\n\n---\n\n### **Recurring Failure Patterns**\n\n#### **Pattern 1: Multi-word titles broken across OCR lines**\n- **Appears in:** Iteration 14 (Labaneh Balls with Nigella Seeds)\n- **Issue:** When OCR splits a title across 4+ lines, the algorithm only generates joins up to 3 consecutive lines. The full title never enters the candidate pool. Shorter overlapping fragments then win via dedup (\"shorter wins\" rule).\n- **Why it recurs:** The 3-line join ceiling has been constant since iteration 1. This is a design constraint, not a bug in recent changes.\n\n#### **Pattern 2: Structural bonus overrides mixed-case legitimate titles**\n- **Appears in:** Iteration 14 (Smażona zielona fasolka), indirectly in earlier iterations\n- **Issue:** The +0.10 structural heading bonus for ALL_CAPS candidates is enough to flip the winner when the true title is mixed-case (Polish, Italian convention). An all-caps secondary title line (translation/subtitle) beats the actual mixed-case title.\n- **Why it recurs:** The structural bonus is a global constant. It was tuned to prefer all-caps recipe headings (which are common in English cookbooks), but it creates systematic bias against non-English typography conventions.\n\n#### **Pattern 3: Bilingual detection threshold is fragile and narrow in scope**\n- **Appears in:** Iteration 11 (CHLEBEK false positive), Iteration 14 (Smażona zielona cross-lingual pair)\n- **Issue:** The 0.4 cosine similarity threshold for detecting translation pairs only works reliably for closely related language pairs (Polish ↔ English). Cross-lingual pairs like Polish ↔ Korean romanization fall below 0.4. The detection also only checks position 0 (mixed-case) + positions 1–2 (all-caps), so it misses translations at other positions.\n- **Why it recurs:** The threshold is a magic constant calibrated against a narrow set of examples. New language combinations expose its brittleness.\n\n#### **Pattern 4: Incomplete ingredient/list detection**\n- **Appeared in:** Iteration 12 (12 bullet-line failures)\n- **Status:** Fixed by changes in iteration 12 (bullet filter + section label filter + expanded `looksLikeIngredient`)\n- **Note:** The fix was comprehensive at the candidate-generation stage, so it does not recur in iterations 13–14.\n\n#### **Pattern 5: Dedup \"shorter wins\" removes valid longer candidates**\n- **Appears in:** Iteration 14 (WITH NIGELLA substring of LABANEH BALLS WITH NIGELLA)\n- **Issue:** The dedup rule unconditionally prefers shorter candidates when one is a substring of another. This is correct for `Pierogi Ruskie` vs. `Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki`, but breaks when a shorter overlapping substring is a semantic fragment (never intended to be a title) rather than a more focused version of the same title.\n- **Why it recurs:** The dedup rule is a core heuristic that has been stable since iteration 5. Recent fixes (iteration 11–12) added guards to prevent sub-section headers from entering the pool in the first place, but they don't address the dedup rule's blind spot: overlapping candidates where neither is a clean parent/child relationship.\n\n#### **Pattern 6: Multi-title guard assumptions**\n- **Appears in:** Iteration 12 (section label `INGREDIENTS` wins), earlier iterations\n- **Issue:** The `isSubHeader` check assumes the first ALL_CAPS heading is the recipe title and checks only the remainder as potential sub-headers. This breaks when document layout is `SECTION_LABEL → TITLE → ingredients`.\n- **Status:** Fixed by section label filter in iteration 12, removing section labels before they reach the multi-title guard.\n\n---\n\n### **High-Level Patterns**\n\n1. **Language-specific gaps:** Each iteration uncovers patterns absent from previous language coverage (Polish measurement units, Polish metadata, non-English capitalization conventions).\n\n2. **Threshold brittleness:** Magic constants (`0.4` similarity, `+0.10` structural bonus, `3-line` join ceiling) work for the corpus they were tuned against but break on edge cases.\n\n3. **Cascading precondition dependencies:** Downstream guards (dedup, multi-title guard, prefix removal) often depend on upstream conditions (full title presence in `selected`). When an earlier stage suppresses the full title, later guards become ineffective.\n\n4. **Structural heuristics vs. content signals:** The algorithm increasingly relies on typographic structure (ALL_CAPS, section positions, bullet markers) to avoid embedding-score errors, but structure is language/cookbook-specific. Non-English cookbooks and OCR-mangled formatting break these assumptions.\n\n5. **OCR fragmentation:** The 3-line join ceiling and pre-merge continuation logic handle some line breaks but not arbitrary multi-line splits of titles."}],"totalDurationMs":32010,"totalTokens":76596,"totalToolUseCount":11,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1900,"cache_read_input_tokens":73073,"output_tokens":1620,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1900},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
